author: COMSOL
description: This example studies the cooling effects of a disk-stack heat sink on an electronic component. The heat sink consists of several thin aluminum disks piled up around a central hollow column. Such a configuration allows cooling of large surfaces of aluminum fins by air at ambient temperature.
label: disk_stack_heat_sink.mph
